Description: Egyptian-style nude female terracotta figure with a column/pillar along the back as seen on amulets of Isis-Hathor. Traces of a thick white coating. Red-brown Nile silt fabric. Base is missing. Mould-made and solid. Red-brown Nile silt with grey surfaces and core, abundant mica and sand inclusions. Body missing head.
Curator's comments: Found unregistered, but with labels from the EEF stating they were from Petrie's excavations at Naukratis in 1885; however, objects from Kamiros were also in this box.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (DC.030) (Phase 3)
